{"ClientSettings":{"Pn":{"Cn":1,"St":0,"Qs":0,"Prod":"P"},"Sc":{"Cn":1,"St":0,"Qs":0,"Prod":"H"},"Qz":{"Cn":1,"St":0,"Qs":0,"Prod":"T"},"Ap":true,"Mute":true,"Lad":"2026-05-23T00:00:00Z","Iotd":0,"Gwb":0,"Tns":0,"Dft":null,"Mvs":0,"Flt":0,"Imp":1,"Tobn":0},"MediaContents":[{"ImageContent":{"Description":"Naturally sculpted over 500,000 years, the Pont d'Arc in France opens like a gateway to the Ardèche Gorge. At dawn, its monumental silhouette glows with a golden hue as the murmur of the river echoes between limestone cliffs, where peregrine falcons and crag martins nest. You walk along the sandy bank, scented with wild mint and sun-warmed boxwood, with the feeling of stepping into a landscape that has remained unchanged since prehistoric times.","Image":{"Url":"/th?id=OHR.PontArdeche_ROW1049828864_1920x1080.webp","Wallpaper":"/th?id=OHR.PontArdeche_ROW1049828864_1920x1200.jpg&rf=LaDigue_1920x1200.jpg","Downloadable":true},"Headline":"Info","Title":"Pont d'Arc, Ardèche, France","Copyright":"© Gael Fontaine/Getty Images","SocialGood":null,"MapLink":{"Url":"","Link":""},"QuickFact":{"MainText":"","LinkUrl":"","LinkText":""},"TriviaUrl":"/search?q=Bing+homepage+quiz&filters=WQOskey:\"HPQuiz_20260522_PontArdeche\"&FORM=HPQUIZ","BackstageUrl":"/search?q=Pont+dArc+Ardeche&form=hpcapt&filters=HpDate:\"20260522_0700\"+mgzv3configlist:\"BingQA_Encyclopedia_Layout\"","TriviaId":"HPQuiz_20260522_PontArdeche"},"Ssd":"20260522","Name":"PontArdeche","Market":"ROW","Hash":"1049828864","FullDateString":"22 May 2026"},{"ImageContent":{"Description":"Today's image spotlights a drink that connects daily rituals to ancient landscapes. Just one look at the terraced tea fields of Sichuan Province, China, shows how deep those roots run. This misty region in southwest China is one of the earliest centres of tea culture, where people drank and cultivated tea more than 2,000 years ago. On nearby Mengding Mountain, a scholar named Wu Lizhen planted some of the world's first managed tea gardens during the Han Dynasty, laying the groundwork for generations of growers.","Image":{"Url":"/th?id=OHR.SichuanTea_ROW1006834324_1920x1080.webp","Wallpaper":"/th?id=OHR.SichuanTea_ROW1006834324_1920x1200.jpg&rf=LaDigue_1920x1200.jpg","Downloadable":true},"Headline":"Info","Title":"Tea terraces in Sichuan Province, China","Copyright":"© lzf/Shutterstock","SocialGood":null,"MapLink":{"Url":"","Link":""},"QuickFact":{"MainText":"","LinkUrl":"","LinkText":""},"TriviaUrl":"/search?q=Bing+homepage+quiz&filters=WQOskey:\"HPQuiz_20260521_SichuanTea\"&FORM=HPQUIZ","BackstageUrl":"/search?q=Tea+terraces+in+Sichuan+Province&form=hpcapt&filters=HpDate:\"20260521_0700\"+mgzv3configlist:\"BingQA_Encyclopedia_Layout\"","TriviaId":"HPQuiz_20260521_SichuanTea"},"Ssd":"20260521","Name":"SichuanTea","Market":"ROW","Hash":"1006834324","FullDateString":"21 May 2026"},{"ImageContent":{"Description":"A soft buzz and a dusting of pollen can shape the future of our food. Today's image features the bumble bee during its quiet yet essential work. Unlike many insects, bumble bees use 'buzz pollination,' vibrating their flight muscles to shake pollen from flowers—a method vital for crops such as tomatoes, peppers and blueberries. Bees and other pollinators contribute to more than 75% of the world's major food crops, improving both yield and quality.","Image":{"Url":"/th?id=OHR.BumbleBee_ROW7621208242_1920x1080.webp","Wallpaper":"/th?id=OHR.BumbleBee_ROW7621208242_1920x1200.jpg&rf=LaDigue_1920x1200.jpg","Downloadable":true},"Headline":"Info","Title":"Bumble bee pollinating, Worcester, England","Copyright":"© SimonEastwood87/Shutterstock","SocialGood":null,"MapLink":{"Url":"","Link":""},"QuickFact":{"MainText":"","LinkUrl":"","LinkText":""},"TriviaUrl":"/search?q=Bing+homepage+quiz&filters=WQOskey:\"HPQuiz_20260520_BumbleBee\"&FORM=HPQUIZ","BackstageUrl":"/search?q=Bumblebee&form=hpcapt&filters=HpDate:\"20260520_0700\"+mgzv3configlist:\"BingQA_Encyclopedia_Layout\"","TriviaId":"HPQuiz_20260520_BumbleBee"},"Ssd":"20260520","Name":"BumbleBee","Market":"ROW","Hash":"7621208242","FullDateString":"20 May 2026"},{"ImageContent":{"Description":"At Mallorca's far northern tip, in Spain's Balearic Islands, the Formentor Lighthouse stands on the sheer cliffs of Cap de Formentor. This exposed headland is often called the 'Meeting of the Winds.' Built in 1863 and first lit on September 30 of that year, the lighthouse rises about 210 metres above the Mediterranean Sea and is reached by a narrow, switchback road about 13 kilometres from Port de Pollença. Under your feet is pale limestone—rock formed from ancient marine life and later lifted and carved by erosion into dramatic faces, sea caves and natural arches. This rugged geology gives rise to the area's stark beauty and sense of isolation. Want to earn the view? Follow one of the peninsula's hiking routes, or tackle the short, steep climb to Talaia d'Albercutx for a watchtower panorama before continuing to the lighthouse. Keep an eye on the slopes: wild goats, descended from early domestic herds, spring across the ledges with effortless balance.","Image":{"Url":"/th?id=OHR.SpainLighthouse_ROW0931685772_1920x1080.webp","Wallpaper":"/th?id=OHR.SpainLighthouse_ROW0931685772_1920x1200.jpg&rf=LaDigue_1920x1200.jpg","Downloadable":true},"Headline":"Info","Title":"Formentor Lighthouse, Mallorca, Balearic Islands, Spain","Copyright":"© Allard Schager/Getty Images","SocialGood":null,"MapLink":{"Url":"","Link":""},"QuickFact":{"MainText":"","LinkUrl":"","LinkText":""},"TriviaUrl":"/search?q=Bing+homepage+quiz&filters=WQOskey:\"HPQuiz_20260519_SpainLighthouse\"&FORM=HPQUIZ","BackstageUrl":"/search?q=Formentor+Lighthouse+Spain&form=hpcapt&filters=HpDate:\"20260519_0700\"+mgzv3configlist:\"BingQA_Encyclopedia_Layout\"","TriviaId":"HPQuiz_20260519_SpainLighthouse"},"Ssd":"20260519","Name":"SpainLighthouse","Market":"ROW","Hash":"0931685772","FullDateString":"19 May 2026"},{"ImageContent":{"Description":"Some people chase peaks, others follow lakes. In Wales, the Snowdonia (Eryri) National Park is one stop that quietly combines both—Dolbadarn Castle. Standing beside the serene waters of Llyn Padarn, this 13th-century fortress was built by Llywelyn the Great—Prince of Gwynedd from 1199 to 1240—to guard the route through Llanberis Pass. Built from purple and green slate, the castle was largely assembled using dry stone techniques without mortar, apart from the keep. Its distinctive round tower once stood watch over the valley. History here has its twists. Owain Goch ap Gruffudd, Llywelyn's nephew, is believed to have been imprisoned inside these walls after a family feud.","Image":{"Url":"/th?id=OHR.NPFortnight2026_ROW9483729156_1920x1080.webp","Wallpaper":"/th?id=OHR.NPFortnight2026_ROW9483729156_1920x1200.jpg&rf=LaDigue_1920x1200.jpg","Downloadable":true},"Headline":"Info","Title":"Dolbadarn Castle, Llanberis, Wales","Copyright":"© Allan Hartley/Alamy","SocialGood":null,"MapLink":{"Url":"","Link":""},"QuickFact":{"MainText":"","LinkUrl":"","LinkText":""},"TriviaUrl":"/search?q=Bing+homepage+quiz&filters=WQOskey:\"HPQuiz_20260518_NPFortnight2026\"&FORM=HPQUIZ","BackstageUrl":"/search?q=Dolbadarn+Castle+Wales&form=hpcapt&filters=HpDate:\"20260518_0700\"+mgzv3configlist:\"BingQA_Encyclopedia_Layout\"","TriviaId":"HPQuiz_20260518_NPFortnight2026"},"Ssd":"20260518","Name":"NPFortnight2026","Market":"ROW","Hash":"9483729156","FullDateString":"18 May 2026"},{"ImageContent":{"Description":"How high is high enough for a great view? In the eastern United States, it doesn't take much. Hawksbill Mountain is the highest point in Shenandoah National Park, Virginia, at 1,234 metres, showing how these older mountains rely on openness, not elevation. The park's establishment in 1935 involved reforestation after extensive farming and logging. Today, much of that land has returned to forest, supporting mixed hardwoods, mountain laurel and rhododendron. What else? Some of the rocks found here date back over 1 billion years, among the oldest in the state. The park shelters over 200 bird species and 32 species of fish and remains dog friendly, allowing pets in campgrounds and on most trails.","Image":{"Url":"/th?id=OHR.ShenandoahSunset_ROW7042145908_1920x1080.webp","Wallpaper":"/th?id=OHR.ShenandoahSunset_ROW7042145908_1920x1200.jpg&rf=LaDigue_1920x1200.jpg","Downloadable":true},"Headline":"Info","Title":"Hawksbill Mountain in Shenandoah National Park, Virginia, United States","Copyright":"© John Baggaley/Getty Images","SocialGood":null,"MapLink":{"Url":"","Link":""},"QuickFact":{"MainText":"","LinkUrl":"","LinkText":""},"TriviaUrl":"/search?q=Bing+homepage+quiz&filters=WQOskey:\"HPQuiz_20260517_ShenandoahSunset\"&FORM=HPQUIZ","BackstageUrl":"/search?q=Hawksbill+Mountain&form=hpcapt&filters=HpDate:\"20260517_0700\"+mgzv3configlist:\"BingQA_Encyclopedia_Layout\"","TriviaId":"HPQuiz_20260517_ShenandoahSunset"},"Ssd":"20260517","Name":"ShenandoahSunset","Market":"ROW","Hash":"7042145908","FullDateString":"17 May 2026"},{"ImageContent":{"Description":"What do you call a place where the rocks do the climbing, and humans try to keep up? Welcome to Smith Rock State Park in Oregon, United States, where cliffs rise fast, and excuses fall faster. It sits inside the 40-kilometre-long Crooked River Caldera, shaped by multiple volcanic eruptions. Its welded tuff cliffs are made from compressed volcanic ash that cooled under pressure. The Crooked River carved the canyon, while formations like the Spire rise up to 180 metres.","Image":{"Url":"/th?id=OHR.SmithRockPark_ROW6845039893_1920x1080.webp","Wallpaper":"/th?id=OHR.SmithRockPark_ROW6845039893_1920x1200.jpg&rf=LaDigue_1920x1200.jpg","Downloadable":true},"Headline":"Info","Title":"Smith Rock State Park, Oregon, United States","Copyright":"© Alex Ratson/Getty Images","SocialGood":null,"MapLink":{"Url":"","Link":""},"QuickFact":{"MainText":"","LinkUrl":"","LinkText":""},"TriviaUrl":"/search?q=Bing+homepage+quiz&filters=WQOskey:\"HPQuiz_20260516_SmithRockPark\"&FORM=HPQUIZ","BackstageUrl":"/search?q=Smith+Rock+State+Park&form=hpcapt&filters=HpDate:\"20260516_0700\"+mgzv3configlist:\"BingQA_Encyclopedia_Layout\"","TriviaId":"HPQuiz_20260516_SmithRockPark"},"Ssd":"20260516","Name":"SmithRockPark","Market":"ROW","Hash":"6845039893","FullDateString":"16 May 2026"}],"PreloadMediaContents":[{"ImageContent":{"Description":"In Sagarmatha National Park, Nepal, Mount Everest rises into view, calm and unmoved as evening settles in. That stillness was broken in 1953. After years of planning and weeks of climbing, New Zealander Edmund Hillary and Sherpa mountaineer Tenzing Norgay reached the summit. At just under 8,850 metres above sea level, they became the first people known to have stood at Earth's highest point.","Image":{"Url":"/th?id=OHR.SummitEverest_ROW0124036396_1920x1080.webp","Wallpaper":"/th?id=OHR.SummitEverest_ROW0124036396_1920x1200.jpg&rf=LaDigue_1920x1200.jpg","Downloadable":true},"Headline":"Info","Title":"Mount Everest summit, Sagarmatha National Park, Nepal","Copyright":"© fotoVoyager/Getty Images","SocialGood":null,"MapLink":{"Url":"","Link":""},"QuickFact":{"MainText":"","LinkUrl":"","LinkText":""},"TriviaUrl":"/search?q=Bing+homepage+quiz&filters=WQOskey:\"HPQuiz_20260529_SummitEverest\"&FORM=HPQUIZ","BackstageUrl":"/search?q=Mount+Everest&form=hpcapt&filters=HpDate:\"20260529_0700\"+mgzv3configlist:\"BingQA_Encyclopedia_Layout\"","TriviaId":"HPQuiz_20260529_SummitEverest"},"Ssd":"20260529","Name":"SummitEverest","Market":"ROW","Hash":"0124036396","FullDateString":"29 May 2026"},{"ImageContent":{"Description":"As night settles over Suwon, South Korea, the old city wall pictured here shows that function doesn't necessarily cancel out beauty—it can create it. Built between 1794 and 1796 under King Jeongjo of the Joseon Dynasty, Hwaseong Fortress was more than a barrier. It was policy in stone: a reform-minded push for a leaner, better-run state, driven by practicality and a deeply personal motive. Jeongjo ordered its construction to honour his father while strengthening a kingdom that wanted smarter systems, not just thicker walls.","Image":{"Url":"/th?id=OHR.HwaesongFortress_ROW5120424335_1920x1080.webp","Wallpaper":"/th?id=OHR.HwaesongFortress_ROW5120424335_1920x1200.jpg&rf=LaDigue_1920x1200.jpg","Downloadable":true},"Headline":"Info","Title":"Old city wall of Hwaseong Fortress, Suwon, South Korea","Copyright":"© aomam/Getty Images","SocialGood":null,"MapLink":{"Url":"","Link":""},"QuickFact":{"MainText":"","LinkUrl":"","LinkText":""},"TriviaUrl":"/search?q=Bing+homepage+quiz&filters=WQOskey:\"HPQuiz_20260528_HwaesongFortress\"&FORM=HPQUIZ","BackstageUrl":"/search?q=Hwaseong+Fortress+Suwon&form=hpcapt&filters=HpDate:\"20260528_0700\"+mgzv3configlist:\"BingQA_Encyclopedia_Layout\"","TriviaId":"HPQuiz_20260528_HwaesongFortress"},"Ssd":"20260528","Name":"HwaesongFortress","Market":"ROW","Hash":"5120424335","FullDateString":"28 May 2026"},{"ImageContent":{"Description":"Just look at this cutie swimming in the waters of Kachemak Bay in Alaska! Otters are captivating creatures that play an essential role in maintaining healthy ecosystems. Known for their playful behaviour and remarkable intelligence, otters are key indicators of waterway health. Sadly, they face growing challenges from habitat loss and pollution.","Image":{"Url":"/th?id=OHR.OtterDay_ROW8950256578_1920x1080.webp","Wallpaper":"/th?id=OHR.OtterDay_ROW8950256578_1920x1200.jpg&rf=LaDigue_1920x1200.jpg","Downloadable":true},"Headline":"Info","Title":"Sea otter, Kachemak Bay, Homer, Alaska, United States","Copyright":"© roclwyr/Getty Images","SocialGood":null,"MapLink":{"Url":"","Link":""},"QuickFact":{"MainText":"","LinkUrl":"","LinkText":""},"TriviaUrl":"/search?q=Bing+homepage+quiz&filters=WQOskey:\"HPQuiz_20260527_OtterDay\"&FORM=HPQUIZ","BackstageUrl":"/search?q=Sea+Otter&form=hpcapt&filters=HpDate:\"20260527_0700\"+mgzv3configlist:\"BingQA_Encyclopedia_Layout\"","TriviaId":"HPQuiz_20260527_OtterDay"},"Ssd":"20260527","Name":"OtterDay","Market":"ROW","Hash":"8950256578","FullDateString":"27 May 2026"},{"ImageContent":{"Description":"As spring sweeps across Northern California in the United States, the landscape is transformed by the vibrant displays of lupine flowers in shades of blue, purple and white. Flourishing in the region's Mediterranean climate, these wildflowers provide a vital source of nectar for pollinators such as bees, butterflies and beetles. With over 200 species found worldwide, lupines range from coastal varieties to those that thrive in mountain meadows. Beyond their striking beauty, lupines are essential to the ecosystem: by fixing nitrogen underground, they enrich soil fertility and support the growth of surrounding plants, even in nutrient-poor environments.","Image":{"Url":"/th?id=OHR.LupineBloom_ROW8766643120_1920x1080.webp","Wallpaper":"/th?id=OHR.LupineBloom_ROW8766643120_1920x1200.jpg&rf=LaDigue_1920x1200.jpg","Downloadable":true},"Headline":"Info","Title":"Lupine flowers in bloom, Northern California, United States","Copyright":"© Jeffrey Lewis/Tandem Stills + Motion","SocialGood":null,"MapLink":{"Url":"","Link":""},"QuickFact":{"MainText":"","LinkUrl":"","LinkText":""},"TriviaUrl":"/search?q=Bing+homepage+quiz&filters=WQOskey:\"HPQuiz_20260526_LupineBloom\"&FORM=HPQUIZ","BackstageUrl":"/search?q=Lupinus&form=hpcapt&filters=HpDate:\"20260526_0700\"+mgzv3configlist:\"BingQA_Encyclopedia_Layout\"","TriviaId":"HPQuiz_20260526_LupineBloom"},"Ssd":"20260526","Name":"LupineBloom","Market":"ROW","Hash":"8766643120","FullDateString":"26 May 2026"},{"ImageContent":{"Description":"What if a building could breathe? In the middle of Jaipur, Hawa Mahal does exactly that—pulling in air, pushing out heat and turning architecture into a quiet science experiment. It's less a palace, more a perfectly timed exhale. And yes, it really does live up to its name: the 'Palace of Winds.'","Image":{"Url":"/th?id=OHR.HawaMahal2026_ROW8601655471_1920x1080.webp","Wallpaper":"/th?id=OHR.HawaMahal2026_ROW8601655471_1920x1200.jpg&rf=LaDigue_1920x1200.jpg","Downloadable":true},"Headline":"Info","Title":"View over Jaipur from Hawa Mahal, Rajasthan","Copyright":"© byheaven/Getty Images","SocialGood":null,"MapLink":{"Url":"","Link":""},"QuickFact":{"MainText":"","LinkUrl":"","LinkText":""},"TriviaUrl":"/search?q=Bing+homepage+quiz&filters=WQOskey:\"HPQuiz_20260525_HawaMahal2026\"&FORM=HPQUIZ","BackstageUrl":"/search?q=Hawa+Mahal&form=hpcapt&filters=HpDate:\"20260525_0700\"+mgzv3configlist:\"BingQA_Encyclopedia_Layout\"","TriviaId":"HPQuiz_20260525_HawaMahal2026"},"Ssd":"20260525","Name":"HawaMahal2026","Market":"ROW","Hash":"8601655471","FullDateString":"25 May 2026"},{"ImageContent":{"Description":"Today's image highlights a prime example of long-term conservation efforts: Tre Cime Nature Park in northern Italy. Located in the Dolomites—a UNESCO World Heritage Site known for striking geology—the park was established in 1981. It is best known for the Tre Cime di Lavaredo: three towering dolomite peaks that rise sharply above alpine meadows. Their sheer rock faces make them among the Alps' most recognisable landmarks.","Image":{"Url":"/th?id=OHR.DolomitesPark_ROW8331574098_1920x1080.webp","Wallpaper":"/th?id=OHR.DolomitesPark_ROW8331574098_1920x1200.jpg&rf=LaDigue_1920x1200.jpg","Downloadable":true},"Headline":"Info","Title":"Tre Cime Nature Park, South Tyrol, Italy","Copyright":"© Adisorn Fineday Chutikunakorn/Getty Images","SocialGood":null,"MapLink":{"Url":"","Link":""},"QuickFact":{"MainText":"","LinkUrl":"","LinkText":""},"TriviaUrl":"/search?q=Bing+homepage+quiz&filters=WQOskey:\"HPQuiz_20260524_DolomitesPark\"&FORM=HPQUIZ","BackstageUrl":"/search?q=Tre+Cime+Nature+Park&form=hpcapt&filters=HpDate:\"20260524_0700\"+mgzv3configlist:\"BingQA_Encyclopedia_Layout\"","TriviaId":"HPQuiz_20260524_DolomitesPark"},"Ssd":"20260524","Name":"DolomitesPark","Market":"ROW","Hash":"8331574098","FullDateString":"24 May 2026"},{"ImageContent":{"Description":"Turtles are not only fascinating animals; they also play vital roles in nature. Sea turtles help keep seagrass beds and coral reefs healthy, while freshwater and land counterparts support balanced ecosystems. Their shells are part of their skeletons, formed from dozens of fused bones, and some species navigate using Earth's magnetic field to return to the beaches where they hatched.","Image":{"Url":"/th?id=OHR.ThreeTurtlesButterflies_ROW8158760119_1920x1080.webp","Wallpaper":"/th?id=OHR.ThreeTurtlesButterflies_ROW8158760119_1920x1200.jpg&rf=LaDigue_1920x1200.jpg","Downloadable":true},"Headline":"Info","Title":"Turtles with butterflies","Copyright":"© Patrick Gallet/Getty Images","SocialGood":null,"MapLink":{"Url":"","Link":""},"QuickFact":{"MainText":"","LinkUrl":"","LinkText":""},"TriviaUrl":"/search?q=Bing+homepage+quiz&filters=WQOskey:\"HPQuiz_20260523_ThreeTurtlesButterflies\"&FORM=HPQUIZ","BackstageUrl":"/search?q=Turtles&form=hpcapt&filters=HpDate:\"20260523_0700\"+mgzv3configlist:\"BingQA_Encyclopedia_Layout\"","TriviaId":"HPQuiz_20260523_ThreeTurtlesButterflies"},"Ssd":"20260523","Name":"ThreeTurtlesButterflies","Market":"ROW","Hash":"8158760119","FullDateString":"23 May 2026"}],"LocStrings":{"LOC_HOMEPAGE_VERTICAL_SCROLL_IOTD":"Зображення дня","LOC_HOMEPAGE_VERTICAL_SCROLL_IOTD_LEARN_MORE":"Докладніше","LOC_HOMEPAGE_VERTICAL_SCROLL_DONATE_NOW":"Пожертвувати зараз","LOC_HOMEPAGE_VERTICAL_SCROLL_FACT":"Цікавий факт:","LOC_HOMEPAGE_GALLERY_CARD_TITLE":"Нещодавні зображення домашньої сторінки","LOC_HOMEPAGE_VERTICAL_SCROLL_GALLERY_IMAGE_ARIALABEL":"Зображення головної сторінки за {0}","LOC_HOMEPAGE_ON_THIS_DAY_TITLE":"Історичні події цього дня","LOC_HOMEPAGE_ON_THIS_DAY_IMAGE_ARIALABEL":"Цього дня, {0}, {1}","LOC_HOMEPAGE_SHARE_TOOLTIP":"Поділитися сьогоднішньою головною сторінкою Bing","LOC_HOMEPAGE_WALLPAPERDOWNLOAD_TOOLTIP":"Завантажте це зображення. Використовувати це зображення можна лише як фоновий рисунок.","LOC_MUSCARD_DOWNLOAD_L